
* aliases *

Syntax: aliases [<alias name> <command>/erase/?]

	You can define your own commands:

	 .alias <alias name> <command>

	Example: .alias ^ .people

	After this, you may try .^ cu execute .people (command period when
you define a new alias is not mandatory). 

	To view all defined aliases, use .alias ? and to erase all your
aliases use .alias erase option.

See also: .umacros, .help commands
	